## 8. AI Architecture

### FedEx Data Usage Restriction
Per the FedEx Integrator Agreement (Section 6k):
FedEx End User Data (including rate data) may NOT be used to:
- Determine prices or estimate market prices
- Develop predictive pricing analyses

The Shadow Ledger stores FedEx rate data for operational
reconciliation ONLY. AI price prediction features must be
built on Cactus margin data and client behavior patterns ŌĆö
not on raw FedEx rate data.

### Phase 1 AI Features
1. Invoice header normalization ŌĆö Claude suggests mappings
2. Exception flagging ŌĆö ai_flagged=TRUE on EXCEPTION/DAMAGED/LOST

### Shadow Ledger (rate_shop_log)
Log EVERY rate request async. Never block rating response.

### Event Sourcing (shipment_events)
Never update shipment status. Always append new event rows.
```typescript
// WRONG ŌĆö destroys history
await supabase
  .from('shipment_ledger')
  .update({ status: 'DELIVERED' })
  .eq('id', shipmentId);

// RIGHT ŌĆö preserves full timeline
await supabase
  .from('shipment_events')
  .insert({
    shipment_ledger_id: shipmentId,
    org_id: orgId,
    event_type: 'DELIVERED',
    carrier_timestamp: carrierData.timestamp,
    carrier_location: carrierData.location,
  });
```

