### Non-Negotiable Rules
- Border: always 0.5px ŌĆö never 1px, never 2px
- No shadows of any kind
- No gradients of any kind
- No pure black ŌĆö use ink (#0D1210)
- Form inputs: font-weight 500
- Active nav: forest green only
- Active disputes nav: bloom
- Focus ring: 0 0 0 3px rgba(45,90,39,0.10)
- Mono font for ALL tracking numbers and IDs
- Badges: always pill shape, never square
- Variance columns: bloom color when positive (overcharge)

### Semantic Color Usage

Default state ŌĆö everything is quiet:
  Text:              ink #0D1210
  Borders:           #DDD8D0
  Backgrounds:       canvas #F8F6F2
  Badges:            subtle tint, never loud

Approved / confirmed:
  Badge text:        forest #2D5A27
  Badge bg:          mint #EEF4EB
  No row highlighting ŌĆö approved is the default expected state

Lassoed / dark account mode:
  Badge text:        slate #3D4744
  Badge bg:          #E8ECEB
  No row highlighting

Held / dispute ŌĆö minor variance:
  Badge only:        bloom text #D81B7A on bloom-bg #FCE4F0
  Row:               no fill ŌĆö badge carries the signal
  Variance text:     bloom #D81B7A on the variance column only

Held / dispute ŌĆö major variance (e.g. >$10):
  Row left border:   2px solid #D81B7A (the ONLY moment bloom goes structural)
  Badge:             bloom as above
  Variance text:     bloom

Alert banners:
  Minor:             muted border + canvas bg + bloom text
  Major:             bloom-bg #FCE4F0 + bloom-border #F48CBB

Savings highlights (Portal):
  Number text only:  amber #D97706
  No fills

### The Rule in Plain English
Color lives in text and badges first.
It moves to borders only when action is truly required.
The screen should feel calm until something genuinely needs you.

### The Two Portal Expressions
The Alamo (internal):
  Primary CTA:     forest #2D5A27
  Data density:    Stripe-level
  Spacing:         compact

Cactus Portal (client-facing):
  Primary CTA:     amber #D97706
  Data density:    Apple-level restraint
  Spacing:         generous, more breathing room